     INSTALLATION

          Copy the file GETEM1.0 , GETEM.DOC (GETEM.UPDATES ,GETEM.DOC.GER)
          GETEMLEVELS and the file GETEMSOUND anywhere you want, 
          e.g. Harddisk, Disk or RAM.
          You mustn't put these files together in one Directory, 
          but it would be better.
          The easiest will be to copy the whole Directory.
          
     START
   
      HOW TO START

            Start Getem in the Directory you put it in with the
            Level-File as shown above.  

            (Getem likes to use the CLI ! Please have in mind to have at 
             least a Stack of 5000 Bytes !
            Use:  
                 RUN GETEM1.0 
            as you have a multitasked System !
        
            While using Workbench, double-click GETEM-Icon. 
            (Nice Icon, isn´t it ?)

            If you start Getem from other Directories, where the Level-File   
            is not present (or to start with other, self-made Levels), then 
            you have to add the Parameter F with the name of the Level-File:   
          
            RUN GETEM F PATH_TO_LEVEL_FILE:LEVEL_FILE 

            (e.g. Level-File is in RAM:  RUN GETEM F RAM:LEVEL )

            From Workbench:

            Double-Click GETEM and Shift+LevelFile

            If you add the Parameter " ? " , Getem prints a short help on your 
            Screen, but won´t get start. ( Only CLI )


            If there was any Problem, Getem will open a new Window to 
            run ...
            
 
          Then you will see a chess-alike-field, where there are many little
          boxes in the Window (In the colors of your Workbench-Screen).
          On the top side, you see some Gadgets and the Logo.
          Also there is a Gadget in the top of the Window, in the
          Drag-Bar, named ICON.
          
          Getem will then open a small Window with the Text 
          'Loading: LEVEL_FILE_NAME' 
        
          This will take a while. (Depends on the length of the File,
           the used Computer and the busyness of it...)

          If Getem can´t find the Level-File, there will be the Message:
          'Can´t find the File: LEVEL_FILE_NAME'

          If so, Getem will compute Random-Levels. These Random-Levels 
          can be UNSOLVABLE ! This was build in to play the game
          without any loaded levels and to test the game.

          IF for instance the Levelfile was of wrong Data-Strukture,
          Getem breaks with a warning. ( Thought was usefull to do so)

          Now GETEM loads the SoundFile. This File is a standard
          8SVX-File and can easily replaced. There will be an
          Error-Message if the File couldn't be find. Then GETEM will use the
          Flash instead of the Digital-Sound. When yuo have installed
          'InstallBeep' don´t bother of the new Sounds.


          If all was going wrong or if the Level-File could be loaded,
          then,

     STARTED

          your´re in Demo-Mode. Getem waits for clicking any
          Gadget or Key, while waiting, Getem shows the loaded Levels
          and makes some Graphics FX.

     GADGETS
      
      CLOSE
          
          Must I explain this one ? Ends my Game...


      START
     
          If you click the START Gadget, it starts the
          Game. Only Gadget which is ON when you start.
        
      ReGo

          The ReGo is for playing the same level once more, if you like.
          (And sometimes it is the only way to make the Level...)
          This Function was added to be more succesful, if you made
          an Error. But, beware of the Time ! (Not yet in this Version)
          This Gadget is ON, when the Game was started.

      STOP
    
          The STOP is for stopping the Game. If you can´t see these
          f*@#¡ng boxes anymore, this is the best Gadget.
          Only ON, when Game was started.

      SCORE

          Opens or Close a Window showing the Score of the last 10
          Levels. The higher the Score, the better you are. The less the Time,
          the higher the Score: Score= 60 / Time (s) * 1000.
          Can be clicked anytime. Bool-Gadget.

      ICON
         
          If you click the ICON-Gaget, the Window will be iconified.
          The Window is shrinked and moved to the upper left top of the Screen. 
          If the Window is shrinked, you can Resize it with the ICON-
          Gadget once again. The Game is paused, also the Demo, and
          will be continued at the same Level and build of the Plane.
          This function was build in for reasons of Big-Brothers-
          Watching-You-In-Your-Company...

