     LEVEL-FILE

          You can make your own Level-File !! As many as you want. The game
          will not end at the last level, it'll begin at the first level
          again. First, there are the Levels, then you can insert a name for
          every Level. The name should not have more than 50 Chars. You can
          insert any sort of name like these ones: Timecruncher, Old Trap, Big
          Hole, Lonley One.

          Here the structure of a Level:

              00000000000000       14 Rows, and 14 Columns.
              00000000000000
              70000000000000       0 is white Background.
              07000303030300       1 is Quader
              00700202020200       2 is Cross
              00070101010100       3 is Pyramid
              02027007020250       4 is Circle
              03030700030300       5 is Sand
              04040000040400       6 is Rowy
              77777777777077       7 is Black box (Wall)
              00000000000050
              00000000000000
              00000000000000
              77777777077777

          Do not insert the numbers 8 and 9 ! (IMPORTANT)


          Then insert a blank line (CR) or the Level-Name, to seperate two Levels.

          Structure of Level-File:

          0123
          1223       (Yeah, of course 14 Rows and Columns ! )
          7771
          LevelName1
          3232
          3421
          7651
          LevelName2
        
          etc.


     THE SOUND-FILE

         The included Sound-file is GETEMSOUND. This is a Sound wich
         makes a noice like a Drip of Water. If this does not seems to be good
         enough to you, you can change this file. Copy any 8SVX-File you want
         to GETEMSOUND and you get the new Sound! But be care! Don´t use a long
         Sound! This may cause long waits during the game. Because of speed,
         the Sound is played with the double speed than usual.
    
